home gardens (Kandyan Forest Gardens) alongside pepper, nutmeg, and cinnamon. Larger buds than Madagascar types, milder flavor. Sun-dried processing.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Lower productivity - average 250 kg/hectare. Harvest October-January.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Limited. Would require import from Sri Lankan sources or through regional spice networks. Tropical monsoon proximity to Sri Lanka makes cultural exchange possible."}, {"name": "17. Pemba Clove (Zanzibar Archipelago)", "slug": "17-pemba-clove-zanzibar-archipelago", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 16, "origin": "Pemba Island, Zanzibar Archipelago, Tanzania. Some of the world''s oldest clove trees. Introduced from Moluccas in early 1800s.", "traits": "Hand-picked at last moment before flowering for maximum size and mature flavor. Bright pink when ripe, turn brown as they dry. Significantly higher essential oil content (15-18%) than other world regions. Large cloves with strong aroma and intense taste. Used locally as natural anesthetic substitute.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Very high - up to 40 kg/tree/year for well-grown trees (exceptional trees up to 80 kg/year). Much higher than Indian averages.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Very limited. Pemba cloves are premium export product. Planting material would require specialized import through spice research institutions."}, {"name": "18. Sulawesi/Minahasa Clove (Indonesia)", "slug": "18-sulawesi-minahasa-clove-indonesia", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 17, "origin": "Sulawesi, particularly Minahasa region, Indonesia. Major Indonesian clove production area (Sulawesi produces 40%+ of Indonesian cloves).", "traits": "Strong, pungent flavor similar to Moluccas types. Valued in traditional spice blends.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "High productivity region.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}], "variety_coun